# chezmoi ignore list — target paths (relative to $HOME) chezmoi won't manage.
# Ignored files already on disk are left alone, not removed.

# LazyVim's plugin lockfile is machine-local: lazy.nvim installs the latest
# plugin commits on a fresh machine and rewrites this file rather than restoring
# our pinned versions, so committing it just makes every machine that opens nvim
# show as drifted. Let each machine own its own lock.
.config/nvim/lazy-lock.json
